# Database storage (excluding the seed script itself)
# We track the seed script, but let the database state remain local / seeded at runtime.
# However, for a cloned repo to work immediately, checking in the initial seed db.json is useful.
# We'll allow tracking db.json in git so it clones with the seeded state, but ignore the runtime uploads
